File: Eskom has implemented power cuts. Unsplash/Johannes Plenio JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has announced that the country will go into stage 2 blackouts from 5 pm on Tuesday until 5 am on Monday. The power utility says there is a shortage of generation capacity, owing to delays in returning generators to service. READ: WATCH | State Capture Report | 'Brown helped Guptas capture Eskom' Eskom says it will continue to monitor the situation and implement changes as required. #poweralert1
